results.name: Decimal expansion of Product_{k>=1} (1 + 1/A002476(k)^2).
comment: Let Zeta_{6,1}(4) = 1/ Product_{k>=1}(1-1/A002476(k)^4) = 1.0004615089.. and Zeta_{6,1}(2)= A175646 as tabulated in arXiv:1008.2547. Then this constant equals Zeta_{6,1}(2)/Zeta_{6,1}(4). - _R. J. Mathar_, Jan 12 2021
link: R. J. Mathar, Table of Dirichlet L-series and prime zeta modulo functions for small moduli, arXiv:1008.2547, Zeta_{6,1}(4) and Zeta_{6,1}(2) in Section 3.2.
results.author: _Vaclav Kotesovec_, May 02 2020
